decision_conditions:
Condition : 6 - Prior to the staging of the event in the period between 23rd November 2018 and 28th February 2019, and all subsequent events as hereby approved, survey data gathered from the 2017/18 event must be used to inform a Travel Plan that should be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority.  Unless otherwise agreed by the Local Planning Authority, the survey data should include:
o	Employee methods of travel to the venue;
o	Daily visitor numbers;
o	Surveys of visitors travel choice (on weekdays and weekends);
o	Snapshot surveys of the car park to record capacity at different times;
o	Peak drop-off and pick-up times i.e. a record of arrival and departure times;
o	Records of any complaints received from residents regarding parking on neighbouring streets;
o	A minimum of 5 parking surveys, in accordance with 'Lambeth methodology', shall be undertaken on streets surrounding the site and within 400m of the site's entrance.  These surveys need to be conducted during different periods to assess parking stress in the locality, outside of Controlled Parking Zone restrictions. A photographic record should be provided if possible.
The development shall carried out in accordance with the approved travel plan.
